  "text": "The bulk composition of the melt vein attests that the hot melt was injected into a preexisting fracture and that shearing of the olivine predates melting. Only very little of the olivine crystal was melted by the intruding bulk rock melt implying a maximum melt temperature of $1600 1C. However, as the olivine-ringwoodite transformation is an exothermic reaction accompanied by a volume reduction of 6% [CITATION_1] temperature may have locally exceeded this value.",
